events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 37 points, Josh Giddey had a triple-double and the Oklahoma City Thunder shot a season-high 62.5% from the field in a 145-135 victory over the New York Knicks on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Giddey power Thunder past Knicks

headlines.description: — All-Star point guard Darius Garland was watching the scoreboard, but not his individual statistics on Sunday night. He received a pleasant surprise.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland's career-high 51 not enough, Cavs lose to Wolves

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis scored 25 points and Deni Avdija added 21 to lead the Washington Wizards to their fourth straight victory, 102-92 over the Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards earn 4th straight victory, 102-92 over Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey jumped on Joel Embiid's back and pounded the big man's chest in celebration of the greatest game in the 76ers center's career. The frivolity was fitting because Embiid carried the Sixers in the fourth quarter — all while each bucket...
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores career-high 59, leads 76ers past Jazz 105-98

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored a season-high 31 points and Nikola Jokic had 14 assists as the Denver Nuggets cruised past the Chicago Bulls 126-103 Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter's 31 points lead Nuggets past Bulls 126-103

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis set season highs with 26 points with 22 rebounds, leading the Sacramento Kings over the Golden State Warriors 122-115 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis' 26 points, 22 rebounds lead Kings over Warriors

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis knew he had to have a big game to help the Los Angeles Lakers snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis scores season-high 37, Lakers beat Nets to snap skid
